The paper proposes a new unsupervised reinforcement learning method that can train agents to acquire proactive behaviors in dynamic environments. This work is highly relevant to the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence, and specifically to the sub-fields of reinforcement learning (cs.LG), autonomous agents (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
